\f0\b\fs46 \cf2 East Hampton Clam Chowder\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl320\ql\qnatural

\f1\fs26 \cf2 Yield: 
\b0 6 to 8 servings\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl420\sa140\ql\qnatural

\f0\b\fs46 \cf2 Ingredients\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sl420\ql\qnatural
\ls1\ilvl0
\f1\b0\fs36 \cf2 {\listtext	\'95	}12 tablespoons (1 1/2 sticks) unsalted butter, divided\
{\listtext	\'95	}2 cups chopped yellow onions (2 onions)\
{\listtext	\'95	}2 cups medium-diced {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/celery/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf3 celery}} (4 stalks)\
{\listtext	\'95	}2 cups medium-diced carrots (6 carrots)\
{\listtext	\'95	}4 cups peeled medium-diced boiling {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/potato/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf3 potatoes}} (8 potatoes)\
{\listtext	\'95	}1 1/2 teaspoons minced fresh thyme leaves (1/2 teaspoon dried)\
{\listtext	\'95	}1 teaspoon {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/salt/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf3 kosher salt}}\
{\listtext	\'95	}1/2 teaspoon freshly ground black pepper\
{\listtext	\'95	}1 quart (4 cups) {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/clam/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf3 clam}} juice\
{\listtext	\'95	}1/2 cup all-purpose flour\
{\listtext	\'95	}2 cups milk\
{\listtext	\'95	}3 cups chopped fresh {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/chowder/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf3 chowder}} clams (1 1/2 pounds shucked clams)\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl420\sa140\ql\qnatural

\f0\b\fs46 \cf2 Directions\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl420\sa180\ql\qnatural

\f1\b0\fs36 \cf2 Melt 4 tablespoons (1/2 stick) of the butter in a large heavy-bottomed stockpot. Add the onions and cook over medium-low heat for 10 minutes, or until translucent. Add the celery, carrots, potatoes, {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/thyme/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf3 thyme}}, salt, and pepper and saute for 10 more minutes. Add the clam juice, bring to a {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/boil/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf3 boil}}, and simmer, uncovered, until the vegetables are tender, about 20 minutes.\
In a small pot, {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/melt/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf3 melt}} the remaining 8 tablespoons of butter and {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/whisk/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf3 whisk}} in the flour. Cook over very low heat for 3 minutes, stirring constantly. Whisk in a cup of the hot {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/broth/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf3 broth}} and then pour this mixture back into the cooked vegetables. {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/simmer/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf3 Simmer}} for a few minutes until the broth is thickened.\
Add the {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/milk/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf3 milk}} and clams and heat gently for a few minutes to cook the clams. Taste for salt and pepper. Serve hot.
